{"type":"finding","iteration":16,"focus":"S2-08","id":"finding:S2-08A:lock-held-read-merge-write","title":"Lock-held read-merge-write belongs in the JSONL safety layer, not only in reducers.","reference":[".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/lock.ts:19-31",".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:920-923",".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:958-965"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts","why":"Our helper repairs corrupt tails and appends records, but concurrent append/repair callers still need a lock-held reread before any rewrite or deduped append path.","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","iteration":16,"focus":"S2-08","id":"finding:S2-08B:stable-key-set-union","title":"Set-union merge needs stable record keys, not content-based duplicate detection.","reference":[".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:967-998",".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/DESIGN.md:301"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts","why":"Deep-loop iteration, delta, and graph-event records already carry deterministic fields; a merge helper can union by those keys and avoid silently dropping legitimate near-duplicates.","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","iteration":16,"focus":"S2-08","id":"finding:S2-08C:merge-source-events-recompute-derived","title":"Merge source records, then recompute derived state instead of merging generated outputs.","reference":[".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:1000-1014",".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:1048-1059",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:984-986"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts","why":"A JSONL merge primitive should return a valid raw record stream and let workflow reducers rebuild registries, dashboards, and summaries from that canonical log.","portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","iteration":16,"focus":"S2-08","id":"finding:S2-08D:merge-is-not-admission-control","title":"Merge-before-write prevents clobbering but does not stop duplicate work.","reference":[".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/REVIEW.md:177-184",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts:105-106"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts","why":"The API should be explicit that safe JSONL merge is durability plumbing; loop single-flight and claim/admission semantics still live in lock/lifecycle code.","portDifficulty":"hard","tag":"deep-rewrite"}
{"type":"observation","id":"observation:S2-08:our-gap-jsonl-repair-current-scope","iteration":16,"focus":"S2-08","text":"Our jsonl-repair helper currently truncates invalid tails and blindly appends one serialized record; it does not acquire a cross-process lock, reread the on-disk log, or merge pending records with records written by another process.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts:77-106"],"target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts"}
